                                        </p>
                                        </p>
                                        <p class="card-text">Now, there are ways to improve your odds. If you really
                                            really care about a certain company, reach out to one of their recruiters on
                                            LinkedIn, find a Clark alum there to network with, or tailor your resume to
                                            that specific application.
                                        </p>
                                        </p>
                                        <p class="card-text"> But often people who go that route neglect applying to
                                            most opportunties, and this is a grave mistake. When you see a new
                                            opportunity on here, apply to it ASAP while the applicant pool is small.
                                            After all, a referall may get you to the start of the interview process.
                                            Odds are, so will 10 cold applications.
                                        </p>
